quran[13]{c,v,t}:
  27,23,"I found a woman reigning over them, and she has been given of everything, and she has a great throne."
  27,24,"I found her and her people prostrating to the sun apart from Allah, for Satan has adorned their deeds for them and has thus barred them from the way, so that they are not guided<span class=""h"">—</span>"
  27,25,"<span class=""h"">that they do not<sup foot_note=""80737"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">prostrate themselves</span>to Allah, Who brings out what is hidden in the heavens and the earth, and knows whatever <span class=""h"">you<sup foot_note=""80738"" class=""qiraat"">2</sup> </span>hide and whatever <span class=""h"">you</span>make public."
  27,26,"Allah—there is no god but He, Lord of the Great Throne.”"
  27,27,"He said, “We will see whether you have spoken the truth or have been one of the liars."
  27,28,"Go with this letter of mine and cast it to them, then turn away from them and wait to see what they say to each other.”"
  27,29,"She said, “O chiefs, a noble letter has indeed been cast down to me;"
  27,30,"it is indeed from Solomon, and it is indeed, ‘In the name of Allah, the All-Merciful, the Bestower of mercy:"
  27,31,"You must not exalt yourselves above me and must come to me as Muslims{1}.’”",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is Muslimeenwhich means those who willingly submit to God, regardless of which prophet they followed.
  27,32,"She said, “O chiefs, give me your opinion in this matter of mine. I never take a decision on any matter except in your presence.”"
  27,33,"They said, “We are a people of power and of intense force, and you are in command, so see what you wish to command.”"
  27,34,"She said, “Indeed, when kings enter a town, they corrupt it and humiliate its dignified people, and this is what they<i class=""s"">(always) </i>do."
  27,35,"Thus I am sending them a gift and will see what the emissaries return with.”"
